<p class="drop-cap">I am excited and honoured to announce that my photo <em>The Day I Glimpsed Inside Your Soul</em> will be part of the <strong>Shutter Hub Open Exhibition 2017</strong>, at the <strong>Retina Scottish International Photography Festival</strong>.</p>
<p>[caption id="attachment_1082" align="aligncenter" width="880"]<img class="wp-image-1082 size-large" src="{{ site.baseurl }}/assets/84874-20161122-img_3926-edit.jpg?w=880" alt="The Day I Glimpsed Inside Your Soul" width="880" height="587" /> The Day I Glimpsed Inside Your Soul[/caption]</p>
<p>The photo tells the story of thousands of people who walked through the gate of the Sachsenhausen concentration camp in Oranienburg, on the outskirts of Berlin.</p>
<p>Sadly, for too many of them, it was a one-way journey. Others were lucky enough to live through it. My husband's grandfather was one of them.</p>
<p>He managed to escape from the camp, a few weeks before the Red Army stormed into Berlin. Without looking back, he started the long journey that eventually brought him back home in Italy, after five years of imprisonment.</p>
<p>The photo tells a personal story too, of a grandchild retracing his grandfather's steps, from the train station through the gate, imagining the horror, the fear, the cold. The chill still painfully palpable.</p>
<p>Both men turned their back to the gate and never looked back, 71 years apart.</p>
<p>The exhibition runs from 1st â€“ 30th of July 2017, in beautiful Edinburgh.</p>
